    <text id="d1">
        <body id="d2">
            <!-- [The following two letters are written by Monroe Thayer, Co. C. 10th Mass. Vol. to his friend, Rufus.] -->
        	
        	<div1 type="letter" id="d3">
        		<pb entity="DSSR_000002759_0067"/>
        		<head>Monroe Thayer to Friend Rufus <date value="1863-12-20">Dec 20th 1863</date></head>
        		
        		<opener>
            <dateline>
            <name type="place">Camp Near Brandol [Brandy]<lb/>
            Station VA</name><lb/>
            <date value="1863-12-20">Dec 20<hi rend="super">th</hi> 1863</date><lb/>
            </dateline>
        			
        		<salute>Friend Rufus</salute>
        		</opener>
        		
        		<p>
            I Received your<lb/>
            letter this Morning and I<lb/>
            thank you Very much for<lb/>
            Writing I rote to you a few<lb/>
            days Ago, that I had got<lb/> 
            the Box and I thank you<lb/>
            Very much for Sending it<lb/>
            Because the Shurts Will<lb/>
            Come handy this Winter.  the<lb/>
            Chusnuts Were Very good I<lb/> 
            Suppose Frank Picked them<lb/>
            and I Will Remember him<lb/>
            forever
        		</p>
        		<p>
            Rufus I Belive it Would<lb/>
            be A good Chance for me<lb/>
            to inlist again as you<lb/>
            Say if I Should live
            
            <pb entity="DSSR_000002759_0068" n="[page 2]"/>
        			
            to get through it if<lb/>
            it Would Come handy in<lb/>
            a rany <!--[rainy]--> Day.  I have not<lb/>
            made up my mind What<lb/>
            to Do yet But I Will<lb/>
            let you know in my<lb/>
            next letter if I Do Inlist<lb/>
            I Will Inlist from Hadley.<lb/>
            I Wish I Was up there this<lb/>
            Winter So as to go Down<lb/>
            and Skate a few hours<lb/>
            With the girls I have not<lb/>
            much news to Write<lb/>
            now But I Will Write<lb/>
            Again before long there<lb/>
            is two Men Inlisted <del hand="author" rend="line-through">as</del><lb/>
            out of our Company
        		</p>
        		
        		<closer>
            <salute>I must Close for now<lb/>
            Sow <!--[so]--> good Bye</salute>
        		
        		<pb entity="DSSR_000002759_0069" n="[page 3]"/>
           <seg type="postscript">Monroe Thayer<lb/>
            Co C 10<hi rend="super">th</hi> Mass Vol<lb/>
            Washington D C</seg>
        		</closer>
        		
        		<pb entity="DSSR_000002759_0070"/>
        		
        		</div1>
        </body>
    </text>
